case.name: Searle v Australian Securities & Investments Commission [2006] FCA 208 (23 February 2006)

citances.sentence: ASIC did not oppose the Court granting the leave sought by the Applicant, even in the absence of the conditions that it sought: see [20] above and by way of example, Searle v Australian Securities and Investments Commission [2006] FCA 208. The conditions sought by ASIC were opposed by the Applicant. Some conditions in a modified form were proposed by the Applicant. It is to the conditions that I now turn.
